identificationRemarks: H. rubescens is evidently a species of the SW, and Rocky Mts. I found no records for it in my PNW herbaria search. Some of the leaves are a bit elongated as they often are for H. micrantha the main Heuchera species you are likely to find in the Olympic Mts, one that is usually in notably rocky spots, often in rocky crevices. The elongated, not more rounded leaves, are also unlike any off the other erstwhile similar members of the Saxifrage Family - Saxifragaceae in the Olympic Peninsula.
